          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-18 18:23:45" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to use an attribution in speaking of a person</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to call</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to name</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is not always possible to determine from the context whether the act involved is an initial naming of a person or simply calling a person by a particular name. Likewise in the case of attributions or titles, it is not always possible to determine whether it is a matter of giving an attribution or title to a person or simply a matter of speaking of or to a person by means of such an attribution or title. In some instances the giving of a title may be made indirect. For example, in {S:04000102300022} the statement ‘and they will call his name Emmanuel’ suggests the giving of a title, but the process is stated in terms of how people will speak of this person.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
