          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-18 18:23:45" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to call upon someone to do something, normally implying an appeal for aid</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to call upon</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to appeal to</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to ask for help</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>ἐπικαλέομαι[a] also occurs in such expressions as ὅς ἂν ἐπικαλέσηται τὸ ὄνομα κυρίου ({S:04400202100012}) ‘whoever calls upon the name of the Lord,’ but the meaning is essentially the same as ‘to call upon the Lord,’ since τὸ ὄνομα ‘the name’ may simply be a metonym for ‘the Lord.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
