              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to claim one’s legal right to have a case reviewed by a higher tribunal</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to appeal one’s case</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to appeal to a higher court</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The second clause in {S:04402603200026} may also be rendered in a number of languages as ‘if he had not asked for the Emperor to listen to his case’ or ‘… to judge the accusations against him.’</Comments>
